  "paper_analysis": {
    "summary": "This paper builds high-content single-cell proteo-genomic reference maps of human bone marrow and blood by combining multiplexed surface-protein profiling (Abseq) with single-cell RNA-seq across healthy young, healthy aged, and AML samples. The main result is a quantitative atlas linking up to 197 surface markers to cell identities, differentiation trajectories, and biological states, which is then used to design improved cytometry gating schemes and to map leukemia and rare cell populations more precisely.",
    "measurement_types": [
      "single-cell RNA sequencing (targeted panel and whole-transcriptome)",
      "single-cell surface protein profiling by oligo-tagged antibodies (Abseq)",
      "flow cytometry / FACS",
