    "has_raw_measurements": true,
    "raw_measurement_details": "The paper reports raw single-cell measurements from BM aspirates and matched PB samples, including oligo-tagged antibody counts (97-plex and 197-plex Abseq) and single-cell transcript counts from targeted 462-gene panels or whole-transcriptome scRNA-seq on the BD Rhapsody platform. It also includes raw FACS/index-sorting measurements, single-cell culture readouts, and qPCR validation measurements.",
    "dataset_characterization": {
      "data_availability_statement": "The authors state that the Abseq App is accessible at https://abseqapp.shiny.embl.de/ and that computational routines are available online at https://git.embl.de/triana/nrn. They also refer to Supplementary Data 1 and 2, Supplementary Tables 1-5, Supplementary Videos, and figure source data for detailed access to results and gating schemes.",
      "data_provided_types": [
        "raw",
        "processed",
        "scripts"
      ],
      "raw_data_description": "Raw data consist of single-cell proteo-genomic measurements from Abseq experiments (surface-marker oligo counts plus RNA counts) generated on the BD Rhapsody platform, plus FACS/index-sorting data and qPCR/culture validation outputs. The paper does not specify raw file formats in the provided text.",
      "processed_data_description": "Processed data include integrated UMAP embeddings, cell-type annotations, pseudotime scores, variance-explained analyses, differential expression results, clustering of AML samples, and optimized gating schemes/decision trees. The paper explicitly mentions Supplementary Data 1 and 2 and figure source data as processed outputs.",
      "figure_data_description": "Yes. The text repeatedly refers to 'Figure Source Data' for sample sizes and quantitative values, and to Supplementary Data 1 and 2 for marker associations and differential expression. The figures themselves are based on processed, figure-ready data derived from the single-cell datasets.",
      "scripts_description": "Yes. The paper states that computational routines are available online at https://git.embl.de/triana/nrn, and the Abseq App provides interactive analysis. The text also mentions custom computational tools for gating design and projection.",
      "notes": "This is primarily a single-cell atlas/resource paper rather than a materials paper. The dataset is multimodal and hierarchical: main reference data (70,017 cells, 97 surface markers, targeted RNA panel) plus query datasets (197-plex antibody panels, whole-transcriptome profiling, CD34+ high-resolution profiling, and 12/15 AML cohorts). Data are not just raw measurements; substantial processing is central to the paper, including integration across modalities, cell-state annotation, pseudotime inference, variance modeling, and machine-learning-derived gating schemes. The paper emphasizes accessibility through a web app and online computational routines rather than depositing only static tables."
